# <PROJECT> — Implementation Plan

## Ground rules

1. Do not claim "done" until you have proof. Each task ends with a `# verify` block AND a paired pytest/vitest test.
2. Run code before writing more code. After every file change, re-run the relevant verify.
3. Never invent an API. Verify with `inspect.getsourcefile` / read the installed source.
4. Read the file before editing it.
5. Update `ONBOARDING.md` "Resume here:" in the same commit as the code change.
6. 3-fail rule. If a verify fails three times in a row, stop and ask.
7. Time budget per task: 30 minutes. If you can't finish in budget, stop and report what's blocking.
8. No speculative scope. Only what's needed to clear the current verify.
9. Commit per task. One logical change per commit.
10. Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`, etc.) without explicit user permission.

## Phases

| File | Phase | What |
|---|---|---|
| `plan/PHASE-0-baseline.md` | 0 | Honest baseline |
| `plan/PHASE-1-...` | 1 | ... |

Use the `verifiable-plan` skill to write each phase file.
